{"id": 6177, "date": "1987-02-25T11:00:11", "date_gmt": "1987-02-25T19:00:11", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=6177"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T10:25:10", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-09T17:25:10", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-lucinda-williams-and-bruce-springsteen-disgusted", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/25/meeting-across-the-river-lucinda-williams-and-bruce-springsteen-disgusted/", "title": {"rendered": "Disgusted"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Disgusted&#8221; was recorded by Melvin &#8220;Lil&#8217; Son&#8221; Jackson back in 1951, but it remained in the vault for years, finally seeing the light of day on a 1968 compilation album.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JI_I3Dp8_z8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Lucinda Williams has covered it in concert over the decades, too many times to count; she even included a live performance of it on as a bonus track on her 1998 reissue of her self-titled third album.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-tBNXuQpfPQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>When Lucinda&#8217;s 2006 tour intersected with Bruce&#8217;s Seeger Sessions Tour in London, Bruce made a surprise guest appearance, joining Lucinda&#8217;s band for two songs. One of those songs&#8211;Lucinda&#8217;s own &#8220;Joy&#8221;&#8211;has been floating around Youtube for many years.</p>\n<p>The other song, however, is much harder to find for some reason. So here it is, newly uploaded&#8211;enjoy Bruce&#8217;s only known performance of &#8220;Disgusted.&#8221; (He plays guitar only, no vocals.)</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/j6xYe_1J3HM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Disgusted</strong><br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> November 10, 2006 (London, England)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> November 10, 2006 (London, England)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 December 4, 2018</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce joined Lucinda Williams and her band on stage in London to perform a cover of Melvin Jackson&#8217;s &#8220;Disgusted.&#8221;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69779, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_